    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1543"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1543">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.48/22</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 76.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 10, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose a copy of a
                        letter<note n="1" xml:id="d1543fn1">Not printed.</note> from the French
                    consular representative in Nicaragua requesting me to forward to Granada food
                    supplies furnished by him to certain of his nationals who have had to endure the
                    hardships imposed on foreigners and natives alike by Mena’s lawless bands. The
                    Legation was of course glad to be able to comply with the request.</p>
                <p>I am also transmitting copies of letters<note n="1" xml:id="d1543fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> received from Americans and other residents of Granada,
                    briefly describing conditions which recently prevailed in that city under the
                    Mena régime.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George T. Weitzel.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
